summary: Emir  is a high title of nobility or office.
full_text: Emir , sometimes transliterated  Amir, Amier or Ameer, is an aristocratic or noble title of high office used in a variety of places in the Arab countries and Afghanistan. It means commander, general, or prince. The feminine form is Emira . When translated as prince, the word "emirate" is analogous to a sovereign principality.
title: Emir
